<item>
            <title>[CXF-8310] JMS transport with flag oneSessionPerConnection causes reconnection to not work</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-8310</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using Websphere MQ resource adapter with the flag&#160;oneSessionPerConnection (true) the constructor without the ExceptionListener&#160; is used:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
 container = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; PollingMessageListenerContainer(jmsConfig, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Without the&#160;ExceptionListener the reconnection the MQ queuemanger did not work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How can I use the flag&#160;oneSessionPerConnection (true) and succesfull reconnection.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
